public class LiteralSerializer
extends AbstractSerializer
implements SOAPSerializer

Converts a method and its parameters (Java types) to SOAP payload based on the XML schema provided in the WSDL. This is known as literal encoding.

serialize

public byte[] serialize()
                 throws SOAPException
Takes the parameters in the Envelope and converts them to SOAP payload based on the rules specified in a XML schema. The XML schema is part of the WSDL and appears under the <types> element.
Specified by:
serialize in interface SOAPSerializer
Parameters:

operation - Operation that encapsulates the method name.
parameters - to convert to XML based on the rules specified in the XML schema.
Returns:
byte[] the SOAP payload as a binary.
